The paper deals with the minimum rank of matrices with a specific zero-nonzero pattern, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of the bounds on the minimum rank and the study of random patterns. The use of fields and the study of the behavior of the minimum rank as the field size varies suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a possible sub-category. The study of fooling-set matrices and their properties can also be seen as a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
